HEADWORD: Pennsylvanian
<hw>Pennsylvanian</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>The geological period
from 280 million to 310 million years ago; -- it was characterized by a
warm climate and abundance of swampy land.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Pennsylvanian period, Upper Carboniferous, Upper
Carboniferous period.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A resident of the state of Pennsylvania.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penny</ent>⟦br⟧
